51.6	Flight_attendant	Flight attendant	Flight attendants or cabin crew (also known as stewards/stewardesses, air hosts/hostesses) are members of an aircrew employed by airlines primarily to ensure the safety and comfort of passengers aboard commercial flights, on select business jet aircraft, and on some military aircraft.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/Stewardess%2C_circa_1949-50%2C_American_Overseas%2C_Flaghip_Denmark%2C_Boeing_377_Stratocruiser.jpg/220px-Stewardess%2C_circa_1949-50%2C_American_Overseas%2C_Flaghip_Denmark%2C_Boeing_377_Stratocruiser.jpg
